I remember near wipeouts in TOV from that. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=akanaetendo>Akanae Tendo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 12:23:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are fine</span><hr size=1> We did Royals last night in Chardok, with the NPCs chain nuking 1k+ 2 monks (one lvl 60 w/ AA and one lvl 56) couldnt pull w/o dying once we got to the Prince... poor monks died like 4 times trying to get the king room split =(<br>
<br>
-Akanae Trollhunter 58th druid<br>
-Aawy Meatshield 51st warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxitix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xitix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 8:17:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are fine</span><hr size=1> Alan's response was very informative and states point blank they are aware this makes some mobs too powerful and unless they are special mobs most will get toned down.<br>
<br>
From another angle / perspective. Mobs can be given an effective casting level. So a zone designer could let a level 30 mob cast as if they were 50 or 60. Some did this to compensate for poor npc spell selection as it meant that at least these weak spells would land reliably. Now with the blanket change NPCs are chosing spells well based on this effective casting level. The combination of casting high level spells at high effective level for lower level mobs *IS* way out of whack and will be fixed on a case by case basis. That's the only way it can be done as it's the effective level setting for those mobs that must be tuned not some general setting.<br>
<br>
Hopefully we don't have to wait too long for the majority of the out of whack mobs to be fixed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 8:49:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are fine</span><hr size=1> Akanae Tendo, I pulled Royals last night on my monk (split the death duty with another guild monk) and I was also getting nukes for 1kish. However, it really doesn't matter when trying to split the king. Monks die constantly trying to do that simply because you're pulling 8 or so casters all of which chain cast. There's zero chance to fd. Better to just pull them all an ae imo. Either way, Royals are high enough lvl to have high end nukes unlike the frogs in OS. <p><br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117440" TARGET="_NEW">Seriena,</A> 60 druid<br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=185839" TARGET="_NEW">Joolz,</A> 57 Monk<br>
<A HREF=http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/>Soldiers of Light</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uacterna60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acterna60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 9:08:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are fine</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;I wonder if he's ever seen an NPC gate, summon the party one by one, and kill 'em. That's PC spawn splitting at its finest. :-D &lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Since it's become nearly impossible to split spawns witout dieing, maybe we should get a summon ability.  ;-)<br>
<br>
If they arn't going to nerf the MOBs uber spell selections, then nerf some of their abilities that they got to compensate for being stupid.  <br>
<br>
No more gate+Summon:  Just not fair.<br>
<br>
No more casting through walls:  If I open the door and Uber_caster_Mob_01 starts casting and I close the door, they should get screwed out of that cast.<br>
<br>
No more Uber Melee ability: Caster MOBs were balanced vs. non Caster MOBs before in that they would frequently self mez by chain casting spells when they could be doing the same damage as the non caster MOB by using Melee.<br>
<br>
Give them a recast delay:  MOBs unfairly chain cast way faster than PCs do.  This used to make MONKs job tough since they had to time things just right but at  least they had a couple of chances to try again.  Now, the timing is the same but you get one chance or die.  Might as well send in a warrior/SK/Pally to pull since they clear aggro the same way Monks do now, via death and they have enough HP to take a couple of nukes and get the pull closer<br>
<br>
No MOB gets spells over their level:  Just isn't fair.<br>
<br>
Get rid of the uber channel skills:  Priest MOBs shouldn't get CH off everytime, channeling through 10+ melee's beating on them.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gilth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 9:38:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are fine</span><hr size=1> If they cast a spell way above thier level give it a huge resist penality.  Then resist gear comes into play, you have a bit of risk for getting slammed, but with good equipment and good tactics it can be handled.<br>
